    "tool_response": {
        "bytes": 142419,
        "code": 200,
        "codeText": "OK",
        "result": "# Claude Code Hooks Reference - Key Concepts\n\n## Hook Lifecycle Overview\n\nHooks execute at specific points in Claude Code's lifecycle:\n- **Session level**: `SessionStart`, `SessionEnd`\n- **Per-turn level**: `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, `StopFailure`\n- **Tool execution level**: `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `PostToolUseFailure`, `PermissionRequest`, `PermissionDenied`\n\n## Common Input Fields\n\nAll hook events receive these JSON fields via stdin (for command hooks) or POST body (for HTTP hooks):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"session_id\": \"abc123\",\n  \"transcript_path\": \"/path/to/transcript.jsonl\",\n  \"cwd\": \"/current/working/directory\",\n  \"permission_mode\": \"default|plan|acceptEdits|auto|dontAsk|bypassPermissions\",\n  \"hook_event_name\": \"EventName\"\n}\n```\n\n**Additional fields in subagent context:**\n- `agent_id`: Unique identifier for the subagent\n- `agent_type`: Agent name (e.g., \"Explore\", \"Plan\", or custom agent name)\n\n## PreToolUse Hook\n\n**When it fires**: After Claude creates tool parameters, before the tool executes\n\n**Input includes**:\n```json\n{\n  \"tool_name\": \"Bash|Edit|Write|Read|Glob|Grep|Agent|WebFetch|WebSearch|AskUserQuestion\",\n  \"tool_input\": { /* tool-specific parameters */ },\n  \"tool_use_id\": \"toolu_01ABC123...\"\n}\n```\n\n**Decision control** (use `hookSpecificOutput`):\n```json\n{\n  \"hookSpecificOutput\": {\n    \"hookEventName\": \"PreToolUse\",\n    \"permissionDecision\": \"allow|deny|ask|defer\",\n    \"permissionDecisionReason\": \"explanation\",\n    \"updatedInput\": { /* modified tool parameters */ },\n    \"additionalContext\": \"context for Claude\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## PostToolUse Hook\n\n**When it fires**: Immediately after a tool completes successfully\n\n**Input includes**:\n```json\n{\n  \"tool_name\": \"Bash|Edit|Write|...\",\n  \"tool_input\": { /* original parameters */ },\n  \"tool_response\": { /* tool result */ },\n  \"tool_use_id\": \"toolu_01ABC123...\"\n}\n```\n\n**Decision control**:\n```json\n{\n  \"decision\": \"block\",\n  \"reason\": \"explanation\",\n  \"hookSpecificOutput\": {\n    \"hookEventName\": \"PostToolUse\",\n    \"additionalContext\": \"context for Claude\",\n    \"updatedMCPToolOutput\": { /* for MCP tools only */ }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## SubagentStop Hook\n\n**When it fires**: When a subagent has finished responding\n\n**Input includes**:\n```json\n{\n  \"stop_hook_active\": false,\n  \"agent_id\": \"agent-abc123\",\n  \"agent_type\": \"Explore|Bash|Plan|custom-name\",\n  \"agent_transcript_path\": \"~/.claude/projects/.../subagents/agent-abc.jsonl\",\n  \"last_assistant_message\": \"Final response text...\"\n}\n```\n\n## Stop Hook\n\n**When it fires**: After Claude finishes responding (end of turn)\n\n**Decision control**:\n```json\n{\n  \"decision\": \"block\",\n  \"reason\": \"explanation to show Claude\"\n}\n```\n\nExit code 2 also blocks the turn.\n\n## Key Configuration Patterns\n\n### Match specific tools:\n```json\n{\n  \"matcher\": \"Bash|Edit|Write\",\n  \"hooks\": [{ \"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"script.sh\" }]\n}\n```\n\n### Match MCP tools:\n```json\n{\n  \"matcher\": \"mcp__memory__.*\",\n  \"hooks\": [{ \"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"script.sh\" }]\n}\n```\n\n### Filter with `if` condition:\n```json\n{\n  \"matcher\": \"Bash\",\n  \"hooks\": [{\n    \"type\": \"command\",\n    \"if\": \"Bash(rm *)\",\n    \"command\": \"script.sh\"\n  }]\n}\n```\n\n## Exit Code Semantics\n\n- **Exit 0**: Success. JSON in stdout is processed for decision control\n- **Exit 2**: Blocking error. Stderr is fed to Claude. The action is prevented\n- **Other codes**: Non-blocking error (shown in transcript, execution continues)\n\n## Hook Locations (Priority Order)\n\n1. Managed policy settings (admin-controlled, organization-wide)\n2. `.claude/settings.local.json` (project, not committed)\n3. `.claude/settings.json` (project, committed)\n4. `~/.claude/settings.json` (user, all projects)\n5. Plugin `hooks/hooks.json` (plugin-scoped)\n6. Skill/Agent frontmatter (component-scoped)\n\nSee [Hooks Guide](/en/hooks-guide) for practical examples and troubleshooting.",
